THE formal unveiling of the Tube Awards, a rewarding event dedicated to the television industry will make its debut in February 2022. The executive director of the awards ceremony, Niran Adedokun, made this known in a recent statement. According to Adedokun, the awards ceremony with the theme – Love in a Box – will hold amidst pomp and glee at the prestigious Eko Hotel and Suites, Victoria Island, Lagos.   Fred Amata says lack of awareness troubling health…     Ubi releases debut single Hapu Ya     Afri-Classical concert holds 2022 edition on Jan 30   Tube Afrique, the organisers of the awards, this is the first time in Nigeria the TV industry will be getting a well-deserved spotlight. It will be a night of a mixture of glamour and seriousness, and we are excited to share what we have in store for the industry.” Read Also: Afri-Classical concert holds 2022 edition on Jan 30 - Advertisement - The statement explained further that the Tube Awards is devoted to recognising and celebrating the outstanding individuals who work tenaciously to tell captivating stories that reflect our culture and identity on the small screen. The award will reward achievements in the artistic and technical fields of TV production in Nigeria and Africa. “Despite the technological advancement in TV viewing, TV remains a valuable platform where memorable stories and characters are told and built. So, this is our way of reminding the public why those who bring these stories to life are important by recognizing and rewarding excellence,” the statement said.